edu.virginia.vcgr.jsdl.sweep

Interface SweepToken


  • public interface SweepToken
    The SweepToken interface is returned to callers who use the SweepUtility.performSweep operation to perform parameter sweeps. This token is used because the SweepUtility performs parameter sweeps on a separate worker thread and this token allows the caller to block until all of the sweeps have finished being emitted.
    Author:
    Mark Morgan (mmm2a@virginia.edu)
